Maltese Prime Minister Lawrence Gonzi said he refused a request from the Libyan government to
act as mediator between the Libyan regime and the European Union
over the crisis in the North African country, the Times of  Malta 
 reported , citing comments by Gonzi in Brussels tonight.  To contact the reporter on this story:
